[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rajiv van La Parra: Huddersfield Town sign Wolves winger on loan

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Huddersfield Town have signed Wolves winger Rajiv van La Parra on loan until 31 May, to be followed by a more permanent move for an undisclosed fee.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 24-year-old Dutchman, who has agreed terms on a three-year contract, will complete the transfer in June.
Van La Parra scored twice in 57 appearances for Wolves after joining them from Heerenveen in July 2014.
He was loaned in November for two months to Brighton, where he scored twice in six appearances.
"On one side he has good experience of the Championship," head coach David Wagner told the Huddersfield website. "But, on the other side, he is a good age and has the chance to develop,"
